{
  "stem": "10905.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 1.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And I-- you know, I didn't-- my parents had a difficult time explaining to me that I really didn't need it,  why I didn't need to wear it, and that it was a good thing that I didn't need to wear it.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Because I didn't have the so-called Semitic appearance-- I was little kid, I didn't have the star, I spoke Hungarian perfectly, I ran in the street, I played ball with all the kids.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And as I said, there was no ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "So the kids that I played with were-- could have been young, Jewish children, or they could have been Gentile children for all I know.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, we had to move to Budapest-- right.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had to move to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We-- my father wasn't working.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My mother wasn't working.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had to move-- we moved to Budapest, and had to move to Budapest.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Until the-- near the very end, Hungarian Jews were relatively safe.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, if you look at the history, the Hungarian Jews survived practically the entire war, until near the end of 1944.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "After-- I mean, most of the Hungarians Jews were alive on D-Day.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was only after that that they started getting Hungarian Jews, when that raid destroyed the entire Jewry of all of Europe where they were, but the Hungarian Jews.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So anybody who was from the former Austro-Hungarian Empire, whether you were Czech, whether you were Yugoslav, whether you were Romanian, if you could speak Hungarian, well, of course, you went to Hungary because you were relatively safe in Hungary-- [BACKGROUND NOISE] early on.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Later on, things got pretty bad.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, things got so bad that the-- the SS had to protect the Jews from the fascists.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's how bad things finally got in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
